quote:
Heaven expands;
hell contracts.
Heaven is surrender;
hell is control.
Heaven is awareness spread across all existence;
hell is awareness trapped inside its own echo.

Peace is not the denial of pain;
it is the refusal
to let pain define you.

This is not philosophy;
it is salvation –
the return to what never left.

The wise do not cling to their view;
they gather the fragments of others
and weave them into wholeness.

And sometimes,
you will believe them.
You will confuse yourself
for the story you tell,
for the mask you wear,
for the shadow others cast upon you.

Who looks outside, dreams;
who looks inside, awakes.
Do not fear waking –
it will not take you from life;
it will give you back to it,
whole and unafraid.
